cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a deep learning-based algorithm for compressive sensing image reconstruction, which is a combination of linear mapping and residual learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), as the paper deals with signal processing and data compression. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses convolutional neural networks, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia), and the proposed algorithm is trained using a deep learning framework, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
